  "body": "Failed decode calls like this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n  function f() public {\r\n    bytes memory b = hex\"01\";\r\n\r\n    abi.decode(b, (string));\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nproduce a \"Transaction reverted and Hardhat couldn't infer the reason.\" message.\r\n\r\nIdeally this would be a panic code produced by solc (see https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/13446) but that's not the case right now. We should consider adding a new heuristic for this, if possible.",
