    "body": "@fvictorio I am experiencing a very strange behaviour on my end when testing for `abi.decode` failure.\r\n\r\nIf the function is not `view`, Hardhat throws `Error: Transaction reverted and Hardhat couldn't infer the reason.`\r\n\r\nBut if the function is `view`, Hardhat does not throw anything. \r\n\r\n(However, Hardhat still throws if the revert in the `view` function is due to a custom `error`, a revert reason string `revert(\"something went wrong\")` or a Panic error).",
